### Design System Architecture at Scale

Use a three-layer token structure: global base tokens (colors, typography), product-specific overrides, and component-level variants. Implement CSS custom properties with a naming convention to prevent collisions, and use CSS Modules or BEM for component encapsulation. Document variant combinations explicitly to avoid permutation explosion.

```typescript
:root {
  --ds-color-primary: #0066cc;
  --product-a-color-primary: #ff6b00;
}
.button {
  var(--ds-color-primary, --product-a-color-primary)
}
const Button = ({ variant, size, theme }) => 
  <button className={`btn btn--${variant} btn--${size} btn--${theme}`} />;
```

**Common interview trap:** Creating infinite component variants instead of using composable slot-based components.

