### Real-time Transport Comparison

WebSockets offer lowest latency (full-duplex, 5-10ms) but require sticky sessions in distributed systems. SSE is simpler and reuses HTTP but only supports server→client (requires polling for client→server). Polling wastes bandwidth with frequent requests. For real-time collaboration, use WebSockets with fallback to SSE over HTTP/2 for higher latency tolerance.

```typescript
if (navigator.onLine && supportsWebSocket) {
  socket = new WebSocket(url);
} else {
  eventSource = new EventSource('/stream');
  sendViaHTTP(payload); // polling fallback
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Choosing WebSockets for everything without considering SSE's simplicity for unidirectional use cases.

