### Distributed State with Region-Aware Sync

Implement a state layer with versioning and timestamps to track changes per region. Use operational transformation (OT) or CRDT for conflict resolution when syncing between regions. Cache local state before switching regions and merge changes on region switch.

```typescript
interface StateVersion {
  version: number;
  region: string;
  timestamp: number;
  data: Record<string, any>;
}

class DistributedStateManager {
  private stateQueue: StateVersion[] = [];

  switchRegion(newRegion: string) {
    const currentState = this.getCachedState();
    this.sync(currentState).then(() => {
      this.stateQueue = this.mergeConflicts(
        this.stateQueue, 
        newRegion
      );
    });
  }
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Assuming you can simply overwrite state during region switch without considering pending mutations or cached updates.

