### Multi-Region Observability with Smart Sampling

Implement client-side batching with exponential backoff to send telemetry to regional collectors. Use tail-sampling to capture errors and slow transactions automatically, and probabilistic sampling for normal traffic. Compress payloads and use a dedicated beacon endpoint that doesn't block page lifecycle.

```typescript
class TelemetryBatcher {
  private batch: TelemetryEvent[] = [];
  private samplingRate = 0.1;

  addEvent(event: TelemetryEvent) {
    if (event.isError || Math.random() < this.samplingRate) {
      this.batch.push(event);
      if (this.batch.length >= BATCH_SIZE) this.flush();
    }
  }

  flush() {
    const compressed = compress(JSON.stringify(this.batch));
    navigator.sendBeacon(`/telemetry/${getRegion()}`, compressed);
    this.batch = [];
  }
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Sending all telemetry data without sampling, creating exponential cost and bandwidth issues as user base grows.

