### Multi-Region with Data Residency & Failover

Use DNS geolocation routing to direct users to nearest region, with client-side detection as fallback. Implement service mesh for inter-region communication with circuit breakers. Store user's region preference and cache it; on region failure, failover to secondary with data replication lag awareness.

```typescript
class RegionalRouter {
  private primaryRegion: string;
  private secondaryRegion: string;

  async routeRequest(endpoint: string) {
    try {
      return await fetch(
        `${this.getPrimaryURL(endpoint)}`, 
        { timeout: 2000 }
      );
    } catch {
      console.warn(`${this.primaryRegion} failed, using ${this.secondaryRegion}`);
      return fetch(`${this.getSecondaryURL(endpoint)}`);
    }
  }

  private getPrimaryURL(endpoint: string) {
    return `https://${this.primaryRegion}.api.example.com${endpoint}`;
  }
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Not considering data replication lag between regions—assuming failover is instant and consistent, when secondary region may be stale.

