### Multivariate A/B Testing with Cohort Persistence

Hash user ID with test variant salt to deterministically assign cohorts—ensures same user always gets same variant. Store cohort assignments in localStorage and sync with backend on session start. Use Bayesian statistics for early stopping when confidence threshold is reached. Implement mutual exclusion rules to prevent users being in conflicting tests.

```typescript
class ABTestingFramework {
  assignCohort(userId: string, testId: string): Variant {
    const hash = hashCode(`${userId}:${testId}:salt`);
    const bucketSize = 100 / Object.keys(variants).length;
    const bucket = (hash % 100) / bucketSize;
    return variants[Math.floor(bucket)];
  }

  recordExposure(userId: string, testId: string) {
    const cohort = this.assignCohort(userId, testId);
    navigator.sendBeacon(
      `/analytics/exposure/${testId}/${cohort}`,
      { userId, timestamp: Date.now() }
    );
  }
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Not using deterministic hashing for cohort assignment, causing users to flip between variants on refresh, which skews results.

