### Multi-Region State Architecture

Use a region-specific state store with feature flag middleware that isolates experiment variants per session. Implement server-driven state bootstrap from CDN edge nodes with client-side cache validation and atomic variant assignment via deterministic hashing of user ID + experiment ID.

```typescript
class RegionalStateManager {
  async bootstrapState(userId: string, region: string) {
    const flags = await fetch(`https://${region}-edge.cdn/flags`).then(r => r.json());
    const variant = this.getVariant(userId, flags);
    return { flags, variant, region, timestamp: Date.now() };
  }

  private getVariant(userId: string, flags: Record<string, any>) {
    const hash = hashCode(`${userId}:exp-123`);
    return flags['exp-123'].variants[hash % 2];
  }
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Assuming all users see the same state globally—variants must be deterministic per user, not randomized per region.

