### Intelligent Frontend Observability

Implement head-based sampling with adaptive rates based on error patterns, and enrich all telemetry with trace IDs, variant context, and region. Use a batching collector that compresses payloads and implements backpressure to prevent memory bloat; deduplicate metrics client-side before sending.

```typescript
class ObservabilityCollector {
  async flushTelemetry(traceId: string, variant: string) {
    const batch = {
      traceId,
      variant,
      region: this.config.region,
      logs: this.deduplicateLogs(),
      metrics: this.compressMetrics(),
      timestamp: Date.now()
    };
    await this.sendWithBackpressure(`/api/telemetry`, batch);
  }

  shouldSampleTrace(isError: boolean): boolean {
    return isError ? true : Math.random() < this.adaptiveSampleRate;
  }
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Sending all traces to backend causes network saturation—use client-side sampling and adaptive rates based on error density.

